name: Acronym
description:
An abbreviation that is used as a word. It is formed from the initial letters of a Business Term.
Examples: ERP, EDW, EAD

name: Adaptive Rule Score
description: Score of an adaptive rule executed in CDQ.

name: ADLS Container
description: An asset type that represents an Azure Data Lake Container, which is a logical unit of storage containing Azure Data Lake Storage objects.

name: ADLS File System
description: An asset type that represents Azure Data Lake Storage file system.

name: ADLS Storage Account
description: An asset type that represents an Azure Data Lake Storage Account, which is a logical unit of storage containing Azure Data Lake Container objects.

name: Analytics Model
description: An Analytics Model is a model that examines current and historical datasets for underlying patterns and calculate the probability of an outcome.

name: Application
description: A classification of computer programs designed to perform specific tasks, such as word processing, database management and graphics editing, for a specific business purpose.

name: Assessment
description: A type of asset that is used to store the results of assessments as attributes and relations.

name: Assessment Review
description: An asset of this type is created when an assessment is conducted on an asset and submitted for review.

name: BI Data Attribute
description: A specification that defines a property of a BI data entity.

name: BI Data Entity
description: A unit of data in a BI data source that can be classified and can have a stated relationship to other units of data.

name: BI Data Model
description: An abstraction of data structures such as databases, schemas and files, used to create BI reports.

name: BI Data Set
description: A collection of data that is used for BI report creation.

name: BI Data Source
description: The link between a BI System and an external system.

name: BI Folder
description: A collection of BI content.

name: BI Report
description: A visual representation of data or a collection of visualizations.

name: BI Report Attribute
description: An atomic unit of data that represents a BI report.

name: BI Server
description: A visual analytics platform for creating and storing visualizations.

name: Business Asset
description:
A type of asset that is exclusively used and governed by the business user community. Its instance assets, and all instances instantiating its subtypes, pertain to the business organization. Business assets typically include business concepts like Business Term, Business Process, Line of Business, etc. that help to build the semantics of any organization with insufficient details to build an actual business application.

Part of BG

name: Business Dimension
description:
A set of reference information that categorizes and describes a Business Term in such a way that it provides context and meaningful answers to business questions.

Examples: Business Process, Line of Business, Region, Business Capability

name: Business Process
description:
A set of activities and tasks that, once completed, produce a specific result and added value to the business.

Examples: Campaign Management, Talent Recruitment & Staffing

name: Business Qualifier
description: Business Qualifiers qualify certain assets. This can be used as filters in Business Qualifier Diagrams.

name: Business Rule
description:
Defines or constrains some aspects of specific business data. It is intended to control or influence the behavior of the business data

Examples: Customer Number should be an uniquely identifiable. Country should have valid list of values. Customer Country of origin should be in the valid list of countries

name: Business Term
description:
A word or phrase that is used to describe something or to express a concept in a particular kind of language or branch of business.

Examples: Customer, Person Purchase Count, Loan Amount.

name: Code Set
description:
An enumerated list of valid code values for a specific topic, where the code set is the whole and the code values are parts of that whole. It is a data asset that defines the set of permissible values to be used by other data assets.

Examples: Product Code Set, Person Gender Code, ISO 3166 Country Code

name: Code Value
description:
A valid form of representation for an asset, shortened or covert.

Examples:
In the Person Gender Code, "male", "female", "not known" and "not specified" are represented by the valid code values "1", "2", "0" and "9".
"US" is part of the "ISO 3166 code set" and refers to The United States of America

name: Column
description:
An atomic unit of data that can be stored in a database table.

Examples: FST_NM, EMPID

name: Compliance Self Assessment
description: According to Article 39.1.b. of GDPR, the DPO is responsible for monitoring the organization’s compliance with GDPR. This asset is used to store the characteristics of this assessment.

name: Consequence
description: Outcome of an Event, affecting objectives. This is used to document the consequences that will take effect if a risk materializes.

name: Contract
description: Represents a legally binding contract between 2 or more parties.

name: Control
description: A measure taken to mitigate a risk. Any process, policy, device, practice, or other conditions and/or actions which maintain and/or modify risk.

name: Crosswalk
description: Mapping between two or more Code Sets.

name: Data Asset
description:
A type of asset that represents details of organizational data in two layers. One layer is independent of any particular technology for non-technical stakeholder communication. The other one is taking the implementation system for technical stakeholder communication into account.

Examples: Data Element, Table

name: Data Attribute
description:
A specification that defines a property of a data entity.

Examples: CustomerBirthDate, EmployeeFirstName

name: Database
description:
A collection of data that is systematically organized or structured in order to make it easy to create, update and query the information.

Examples: Ora_DGC_V45, SalesDB2020

name: Database View
description: A Database View is a virtual table based on the result-set of an SQL statement.

name: Data Category
description: A Data Category is a grouping of information relating to an individual, whether it relates to his or her private, professional or public life. Categories are not exclusive. Information may transcend multiple categories.

name: Data Concept
description: A data concept is a high level theoretical representation of the most common data properties of a data domain. A data concept is the business counterpart of a data attribute in a logical data dictionary, just as a data attribute is the logical counterpart of a field or column in the physical data dictionary. (Example: an address is a data concept of the data domain customer or organisation).

name: Data Domain
description: Also known as Data Category or Subject area, this is a container of all the business data domains and data concepts that encompass associated terminology and definitions that an organization is trying to govern. Examples: Master Data (Customer, Product), Reference Data. Business Data Domains group Data Concepts (Year, Date, Address, Name, etc.)

name: Data Element
description:
A unit of data that is defined for processing. It usually documents an aspect of something abstract.

Examples: Person Birth Date, Person Address, Customer Account Number

name: Data Entity
description:
A unit of data that can be classified and can have a stated relationship to other units of data.

Examples: Customer, Employee

name: Data Issue
description: A problem related to issue management; also referred to as issue.

name: Data Model
description:
A diagram that organizes data elements and standardizes how the data elements relate to one another. The Data Model is often used as a communication aid between business and technology.

Examples: Customer Subject area model, Event Subject area model

name: Dataplex Lake
description: A lake is a centralized repository for managing enterprise data across the organization.

name: Dataplex Zone
description: A zone represents a logical group of related assets within a lake.

name: Data Quality Dimension
description:
Represents a criterion relevant for assessing quality and categorizes different aspects of how data quality is measured.

Examples: Accuracy, Completeness, Consistency

name: Data Quality Job
description: Representation of a job executed within CDQ.

name: Data Quality Metric
description:
An implementation of a data quality rule in a selected physical database system using a particular data quality tool.

Example: CRM.ACT.Tx_ID cannot be null and has to be 9 digits and has to follow 999-99-9999 format in CRM system

name: Data Quality Rule
description:
A specification that defines which conditions have to be met to measure the quality level of a data element for its intended use.

Example: SSN must be 9 digits unique identification number for 100% of US personal accounts for Tax processing. Country of origin code should be in taxing country code set for Accounting Business area

name: Data Set
description:
A collection of related sets of Data Assets that are Data Elements or composed of Data Elements.

Example: Customer contact information

name: Data Sharing Agreement
description:
An arrangement between data producers and consumers with terms and conditions including provisions concerning access and dissemination to 'pool' a set of data for specific purposes.

Examples: Sales growth information that is available only for Risk team to generate internal reports only

name: Data Structure
description:
A logical grouping of data elements, where the data structure is the whole and the data elements are parts of that whole.

Example: cfPerson is a Data Structure that contains the data elements cfBirthDate, cfPersonFullName

name: Data Subject Category
description: A way in which a user can interact with data at rest, with manual intervention, to manipulate or consolidate data.

name: Data Usage
description:
An asset that clearly documents how the data can be used between data producers and consumers for specific purpose

Example: Sales growth information that is available to share for read only requirements

name: Directory
description:
An organizational structure that contains files and/or other directories.

Examples: C:/Collibra, D:/Collibra/DGC

name: DPIA
description: Asset type created to store the results of the GDPR-specific Data Privacy Impact Assessment. The DPIA assessment is designed to describe a processing activity, assess the necessity and proportionality of processing, and helps managing the risks to the rights and freedoms of natural persons, resulting from the processing of personal data.

name: Duplicate Score
description: Score of the duplicate analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: End User Tool
description: A way in which a user can interact with data at rest, with manual intervention, to manipulate or consolidate data.

name: Event
description: A potential cause of an incident that may result in harm to a system or organization (ISO 31000). This is used to document the events that can trigger a certain risk.

name: Event-based Review Rule
description: Contains event based rules that determine when a review request is triggered on an asset

name: Field
description:
An atomic unit of data that can be stored in a file.

Examples: FirstName, EmpID

name: File
description:
A collection of data that is treated by a computer as a unit, for the purposes of input and output.

Examples: businessGlossary.xls, dataDictionary05220.csv, datacatalogv25.txt

name: File Container
description: An asset type that represents Cloud File Container.

name: File Group
description: A collection of physical files which together represent a single logical file.

name: File Storage
description: An asset type that represents a Cloud File Storage bucket.

name: Foreign Key
description: Asset type used to model the Primary key - Foreign key relations in relational databases.

name: GCP Project
description: An asset type representing a GCP Project.

name: GCS Bucket
description: An asset type that represents an Google Cloud Storage bucket which is a logical unit of storage containing Google Cloud Storage objects.

name: GCS File System
description: An asset type that represents Google Cloud Storage file system.

name: Governance Asset
description: A type of asset that is used to monitor and advocates to maximize performance or utilization of other Business and Data assets while minimizing the risk factors in alignment with Organisational/Business goals.

name: Issue
description: The parent asset type of all issues.

name: Jurisdiction
description: A hierarchical representation of how a business divides its market on the basis of geography, such as regions and countries. For example, North America is segmented into USA and Canada.

name: KPI
description:
An indicator to periodically measure the success or progress of a particular activity or of an organization, towards a strategic goal.

Examples: Employee Turnover, Customer Attrition, Claims Denial Rate

name: Legal Basis
description: The lawfulness of processing, as defined by Article 6 of GDPR. Personal data may be processed only if, and to the extent that, at least one legal basis applies.

name: Legitimate Interest Assessment
description: Asset type created to store the results of the GDPR-specific Legitimate Interest Assessment.

name: Line of Business
description:
Also known as Business Unit or Business Area, the Line of Business is a logical element or segment of an organization that serves a particular Business need.

Examples: Asset Management, Retail, E-com, Investment Management

name: Looker Dashboard
description: A collection of Looker Tiles with metrics from one or more Looker Looks.

name: Looker Data Set
description: A collection of data that is used to create a Looker Look.

name: Looker Data Set Column
description: A column in a Looker Data Set.

name: Looker Folder
description: A container that stores Looker Looks, Dashboards and other folders.

name: Looker Look
description: A detailed view of a Looker Data Set, with visualizations of findings and insights.

name: Looker Query
description: A query that creates a simple report in a Looker Tile or Looker Look.

name: Looker Report Attribute
description: An atomic unit of data that can be used in a Looker Query and represents a Looker Look.

name: Looker Tenant
description: A platform to create Looker dashboards and rich visualizations.

name: Looker Tile
description: An element that represents data on the Looker Dashboard.

name: Mapping Specification
description: Mapping between two or more Data Structures.

name: Measure
description:
An asset type on which calculations (e.g. sum, count, average, minimum, maximum) can be made.

Examples: Net Sales, Top Customers, On-hand Inventory

name: MicroStrategy Data Attribute
description: A column in a MicroStrategy data model.

name: MicroStrategy Data Entity
description: A unit of data in MicroStrategy that can be classified and can have a stated relationship to other units of data.

name: MicroStrategy Data Model
description: A collection of data that is used to create MicroStrategy reports.

name: MicroStrategy Document
description: A detailed view of a MicroStrategy data model, with visualisations of findings and insights.

name: MicroStrategy Dossier
description: A collection of MicroStrategy chapters and pages.

name: MicroStrategy Folder
description: A collection of MicroStrategy reports and data models.

name: MicroStrategy Project
description: A collection of MicroStrategy visualizations, report attributes and tables.

name: MicroStrategy Report
description: A detailed view of a MicroStrategy data model, with visualizations of findings and insights.

name: MicroStrategy Report Attribute
description: A detailed view of a MicroStrategy visualization, with findings and insights.

name: MicroStrategy Server
description: A visual analytics platform for creating and storing MicroStrategy reports and data models.

name: MicroStrategy Visualisation
description: A visualisation is a visual representation of the data in a MicroStrategy dossier, such as a grid, line chart, or heat map.

name: Network
description: A computer network or data network is a digital telecommunications network that allows nodes to share resources. In computer networks, network-connected computing devices exchange data with each other using a data link. The connections between nodes are established using either cable media or wireless media.

name: Outlier Score
description: Score of the outlier analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: Paper Document
description: A carrier of data in paper form

name: Paragraph
description: A distinct part of a policy, often establishing a particular set of requirements. For example, roles and responsibilities should be established, as they relate to the ownership and quality of data and information for both the business and IT functions.

name: Party
description: An association, corporation, partnership, proprietorship, trust, or individual that has legal standing. A Party has legal capacity to enter into agreements or contracts, assume obligations, incur and pay debts, sue and be sued in its own right, and to be held responsible for its actions.

name: Pattern Score
description: Score of the pattern analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: PIA
description: Asset type created to store the results of the CCPA-specific Privacy Impact Assessment. The PIA assessment is designed to check if a business process adheres to data minimization and purpose limitation considerations outlined in CCPA.

name: Policy
description:
A statement of intent that is implemented by a set of rules. Policies are usually set by a data governance council.

Examples: Personal Information must be adequately protected, Customer Data Deduplication Policy

name: Power BI Capacity
description: A resource that hosts Power BI Workspaces.

name: Power BI Column
description: A column in a Power BI Data Model.

name: Power BI Dashboard
description: A collection of Power BI tiles with metrics from one or more Reports and Data Models.

name: Power BI Data Flow
description: A collection of tables that are created and managed in workspaces in the Power BI service.

name: Power BI Data Mart
description: A datamart in Power BI Service.

name: Power BI Data Model
description: A collection of data that is used to create a Power BI report.

name: Power BI Folder
description: A collection of Power BI Report Server Dashboards, Reports and Data Models.

name: Power BI KPI
description: A key performance indicator of Power BI Report Server.

name: Power BI Parameter
description: A column that is part of a Power BI Report Server Data Model and that is used in a KPI.

name: Power BI Report
description: A detailed view of a Power BI Data Model, with visualizations of findings and insights.

name: Power BI Server
description: A visual analytics platform for creating and storing Power BI Reports and Data Models.

name: Power BI Table
description: A table in a Power BI Data Model.

name: Power BI Tile
description: An element representing data on the Power BI Dashboard.

name: Power BI Workspace
description: A collection of Power BI Dashboards, Reports and Data Models.

name: Processing Category
description: A category of processing activities determined by the actions taken during the processing activity.

name: Purpose
description: An asset that describes the reason for which another asset is created or for which another asset exists.

name: Record Score
description: Score of the record analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: Regulation
description: A directive made and maintained by an authority. For example, BCBS and Solvency.

name: Remediation Action
description: An action taken by the business, to counteract deficiencies or undesirable characteristics.

name: Remediation Plan
description: Steps for carrying out the remediation of one or more issues. The steps typically include options for removing threats and vulnerabilities and priorities for carrying out the remediation.

name: Report
description:
A document containing information that is organized in a narrative, graphic, or tabular form. The document is prepared on an ad hoc, periodic, recurring, regular or as required basis. Reports may refer to specific periods, events, occurrences or subjects. They may be tailored for a specific role and display information targeted to a single point of view or a business unit.

Examples: Monthly Financial Statement, Quarterly Marketing Expense Report

name: Report Attribute
description:
An atomic unit of data that represents a report.

Examples: ExpenseAmount, RiskAmount

name: Review Request
description: Asset that groups all triggers that ask for a review or update to another asset

name: Review Rule
description: Contains rules that determine when a review request will be triggered

name: Risk
description: An uncertain event that could create damage, injury, liability, loss or any other negative occurrence that is caused by external or internal vulnerabilities (Risk Sources), which can be avoided through controls.

name: Risk Source
description: A weakness of an asset or a group of assets that can be exploited by one or more events (ISO 31000). This is used to document the funcamantal source of a risk.

name: Rule
description:
Defines or constrains an aspect of business (data) and always resolves to either true or false.

Example: Where a Business Rule may state that 'A driver must be of eligible age', a Data Quality Rule Spec says 'age must be 21'.

name: S3 Bucket
description: An asset type that represents an Amazon S3 Bucket, which is a logical unit of storage containing Amazon S3 Objects.

name: S3 File System
description: An asset type that represents Amazon S3.

name: SAC Data Attribute
description: A specification that defines a property of a SAP Analytics Cloud data entity.

name: SAC Data Entity
description: A unit of data in an SAC model that can be classified and can have a stated relationship to other units of data.

name: SAC Data Model
description: A representation of a large amount of data.

name: SAC Folder
description: A collection of SAP Analytics Cloud data.

name: SAC Insight
description: A representation of the displayed data source with filters, the navigation state as well as the presentation state of the table.

name: SAC Story
description: A visual representation of pages with charts and tables.

name: Safeguard
description: Safeguards for transfers of data and in particular Personal Information to third parties, other countries or international organizations.

name: SAP Container
description: A collection of SAP DataSphere data.

name: SAP Tenant
description: A visual analytics platform for creating and storing SAP DataSphere visualizations.

name: Schema
description:
An organized structure described in a formal language supported by implementing technology that defines the objects in the technology assets (Table and columns in a relational database, fields in a file).

E.g. CRM_001_PRD, HDP_CNT_CLD

name: Schema Score
description: Score of the schema analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: Security Issue
description: A security incident in which sensitive, protected or confidential data is copied, transmitted, viewed, stolen or used by an individual unauthorized to do so. Security issues can involve financial information, such as credit card or bank details; Personal Health Information (PHI); Personally Identifiable Information (PII); corporate trade secrets or intellectual property. Most security issues involve overexposed and vulnerable unstructured data, such as files, documents and sensitive information.

name: Server
description: A computer program or device that supports other computer programs and their users

name: Shape Score
description: Score of the shape analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: Software
description: Software is a collection of instructions that enables the user to interact with a computer or its hardware and perform tasks. For example, computer programs, libraries and related non-executable data, such as online documentation or digital media.

name: Source Score
description: Score of the source analysis conducted as part of a job, executed in CDQ.

name: SSRS Column
description: A column in an SQL Server Reporting Services Data Model.

name: SSRS Data Model
description: A collection of data that is used to create an SQL Server Reporting Services Report.

name: SSRS Folder
description: A collection of SQL Server Reporting Services Dashboards, Reports and Data Models.

name: SSRS KPI
description: A key performance indicator of SQL Server Reporting Services.

name: SSRS Parameter
description: A column that is part of an SQL Server Reporting Services Data Model and that is used in a KPI.

name: SSRS Report
description: A detailed view of an SQL Server Reporting Services Data Model, with visualizations of findings and insights.

name: SSRS Server
description: A visual analytics platform for creating and storing SQL Server Reporting Services Reports and Data Models.

name: SSRS Table
description: A query in an SQL Server Reporting Services Data Model.

name: Standard
description:
A specific low-level mandatory action or rule that helps to enforce and support a policy.

Example: All personal information has to be encrypted with a specific encryption type.

name: System
description:
Executable software that you can buy commercially off the shelf (COTS), or build internally, to automate one or more business functions that help run a business smoothly and efficiently.

Examples: CRM, ERP, EDW

name: Table
description:
An implementation of Data Entities in columns and rows, in a given database system. It is the basic structure of a relational database.

Examples: Account_tbl, CUST_ADDR

name: Tableau Dashboard
description: A collection of several worksheets and supporting information, shown on a single screen, so that you can simultaneously compare and monitor a variety of data.

name: Tableau Data Attribute
description: A specification that defines a property of a Tableau data entity. Examples: CustomerBirthDate, EmployeeFirstName.

name: Tableau Data Entity
description: An abstraction from the physical implementation of database tables, used for Tableau report creation.

name: Tableau Data Model
description: An abstraction from the physical implementation of database, schema, file, etc., used for Tableau report creation.

name: Tableau Data Source
description: The link between Tableau and an external system. A Tableau data source contains the information to connect to external data, table names, the table relationships, and any customizations that you make.

name: Tableau Project
description: Collection of Tableau workbooks and data sources.

name: Tableau Report Attribute
description: An atomic unit of data that represents a Tableau report. Examples: ExpenseAmount, RiskAmount

name: Tableau Server
description: A visual analytics platform for creating interactive dashboards and rich visualisations

name: Tableau Site
description: Collection of content (workbooks, data sources, users, …) that's walled off from any other content on that instance of Tableau Server.

name: Tableau Story
description: Sequence of visualisations that work together to convey information.

name: Tableau View
description: A representation of your data in a Tableau worksheet or dashboard.

name: Tableau Workbook
description: Collection of sheets. A sheet can be a worksheet, a dashboard or a story.

name: Tableau Worksheet
description: A worksheet is a single sheet on which you can build views of your data.

name: Technology Asset
description:
A piece of information technology (hardware, software, database, software platform) that helps an organization to run a business application.

Examples: Database, File

name: Threshold Assessment Rule
description: Rule that allow to configure the threshold assessments that will allow you to see if impact assessment need to be done.

name: Time-based Review Rule
description: Contains time based rules that determine when a review request will be triggered

name: User Defined Rule Score
description: Score of a custom rule defined by the user, executed in CDQ.

name: Validation Rule
description: A rule that describes a criterion to which content in DGC has to comply.
